      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes can have a mixed impact on small businesses. On one hand, they can lead to increased consumer spending, as workers have more disposable income. On the other hand, they can also lead to higher labor costs, which may strain small businesses with limited profit margins. In a small town with a low cost of living, the impact might be more pronounced, potentially leading to reduced hiring or even layoffs. It's crucial to weigh these factors carefully when considering your expansion plans.",
